`,n.jsxs(t.p,{children:["I once spent ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"a long stretch of time"})," creating sets of images for different screen sizes because I cared about optimized rendering and did not yet have a pipeline that made it painless. Another week - sometimes more - went to ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"SEO on pages I built"}),": meta tags, structure, performance tweaks, re-checking everything twice."]}),`
`,n.jsx(t.h3,{children:"Tests, tools, and the coverage I never quite reached"}),`
`,n.jsxs(t.p,{children:["I cared about test coverage. I really did. There was ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"never enough time"})," to reach what felt optimal. The companies I worked for invested in ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"third-party testing tools"})," because teams needed confidence faster than we could build everything in-house. That function I wrote would not return what I needed; I would stare at it, ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"ship under pressure"}),", and fix it in production - a habit I have since ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"tightened"})," with better checks, reviews, and the patience to verify before merge."]}),`
