`,n.jsxs(t.p,{children:["For much of the 2000s and early 2010s, many sites followed a familiar pattern: the server rendered HTML, the browser displayed it, and JavaScript improved interactivity where needed. ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"jQuery"})," made that layer approachable across inconsistent browsers. ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"WordPress"}),", ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"Drupal"}),", and similar CMS platforms made publishing fast for millions of sites. That stack still works for a large share of the web today."]}),`
`,n.jsxs(t.p,{children:["What changed was ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"user expectations"}),". Search-as-you-type, live dashboards, collaborative editing, and mobile apps raised the bar for interactivity. Teams building long-lived ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"applications"})," — not only articles and brochures — often adopted component-based JavaScript frameworks. ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"React"})," became one of the most widely used options for that job. ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"React Native"})," extended a similar component model to iOS and Android."]}),`
`,n.jsx(t.p,{children:"This article discusses those shifts in neutral terms. jQuery, WordPress, and React solve overlapping but not identical problems. Preferences here reflect the author's experience; your stack should match your product, team skills, and maintenance horizon."}),`
`,n.jsx(t.h2,{children:"What jQuery did well — and where larger apps strained"}),`
`,n.jsxs(t.p,{children:[n.jsx(t.a,{href:"https://jquery.com/",target:"_blank",rel:"noopener noreferrer",children:"jQuery"})," remains maintained and appropriate for many tasks. It unified DOM APIs, simplified events and AJAX, and helped a generation of developers ship interactivity quickly. For small enhancements on server-rendered pages, it is still a reasonable choice."]}),`
`,n.jsxs(t.p,{children:["Difficulties tended to appear as ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"application complexity"}),' grew. Imperative DOM updates — select an element, mutate it, bind another handler — can scatter state across the page. In large codebases, answering "what is on screen?" may require tracing selectors instead of reading a single state model. That pain point motivated declarative libraries, including React, Vue, and others — not a failure of jQuery itself, but a different scale of problem.']}),`
`,n.jsx(t.div,{className:"blog-table-wrap",children:n.jsxs(t.table,{children:[n.jsx(t.thead,{children:n.jsxs(t.tr,{children:[n.jsx(t.th,{children:"Approach"}),n.jsx(t.th,{children:"Mental model"}),n.jsx(t.th,{children:"Often strong for"}),n.jsx(t.th,{children:"Common scaling challenges"})]})}),n.jsxs(t.tbody,{children:[n.jsxs(t.tr,{children:[n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Approach",children:"jQuery"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Mental model",children:"Enhance the DOM in place"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Often strong for",children:"Progressive enhancement, legacy pages"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Common scaling challenges",children:"State spread across imperative updates"})]}),n.jsxs(t.tr,{children:[n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Approach",children:"Backbone / Knockout"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Mental model",children:"Models with bindings"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Often strong for",children:"Structured medium-sized apps (historical)"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Common scaling challenges",children:"Boilerplate and binding complexity at scale"})]}),n.jsxs(t.tr,{children:[n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Approach",children:"AngularJS (1.x)"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Mental model",children:"Full framework in the page"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Often strong for",children:"Enterprise CRUD (historical)"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Common scaling challenges",children:"Large-app performance and migration paths"})]}),n.jsxs(t.tr,{children:[n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Approach",children:"React"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Mental model",children:"UI as a function of state"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Often strong for",children:"Component-driven product UIs"}),n.jsx(t.td,{"data-label":"Common scaling challenges",children:"Tooling choices and ecosystem breadth"})]})]})]})}),`
