`,n.jsxs(t.p,{children:["Tension appears when the ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"product is primarily an interactive application"}),": personalised dashboards, complex client validation, real-time data, and bespoke workflows. Teams then often separate ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"content"})," from ",n.jsx(t.strong,{children:"experience"})," — for example, headless WordPress (or another CMS) for editorial data, with React or another framework for the front end. WordPress has also embraced block editing and modern JavaScript in its own ecosystem."]}),`
